  "page": "History of the Kings-Beyond-the-Wall",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><i><b>History of the Kings-Beyond-the-Wall</b></i> is a book written by Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Herryk\" title=\"Herryk\">Herryk</a> about monarchs of the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_folk\" title=\"Free folk\">free folk</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Kings-Beyond-the-Wall\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kings-Beyond-the-Wall\">Kings-Beyond-the-Wall</a>. It contains the transcription of a song that recounts when <a href=\"/index.php/Gendel\" title=\"Gendel\">Gendel</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Gorne\" title=\"Gorne\">Gorne</a> were called to mediate a dispute by a clan of <a href=\"/index.php/Children_of_the_forest\" title=\"Children of the forest\">children of the forest</a> and a family of <a href=\"/index.php/Giants\" title=\"Giants\">giants</a> over possession of a cavern. They settled by resorting to trickery to make both sides disavow the cavern after the brothers discovered it as part of a chain of caverns that passed beneath the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_dawn_age.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_dawn_age.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=History_of_the_Kings-Beyond-the-Wall&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiaf_the_dawn_age.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiaf_the_dawn_age.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> 